com.gl.vn.me.ko.sample.instrumentation.example.proxy

Class InvocationHandlerExampleC

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gl.vn.me.ko.sample.instrumentation.example.proxy.InvocationHandlerExampleC
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    InvocationHandler

    final class InvocationHandlerExampleC
extends Object
implements InvocationHandler
    This class is an invocation handler that is used by MapProxyFactoryExampleC to create Java-proxy objects.

    Instantiability: allowed.
    Mutability: this class itself has nothing that can cause mutability; depends on the object that was supplied to constructor InvocationHandlerExampleC(Map).
    Thread safety: this class itself has nothing that can cause thread unsafety; depends on the object that was supplied to constructor InvocationHandlerExampleC(Map).

    • Method Detail

      • invoke

        @Nullable
public final Object invoke(Object proxyObject,
                                     Method method,
                                     @Nullable
                                     Object[] methodArgs)
        Invokes provided method on the proxied (original) object. If name of the method to invoke is "get" and the only argument of the method is equal to object that denotes hot or cold faucet valves (see ExampleC), then the invocation becomes tricky: the value of argument is swapped from hot to cold and vice versa.
        Specified by:
        invoke in interface InvocationHandler
        Returns:
        Result of the method invocation on the proxied (original) object. The result can be null.
